{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6b7c84c-5015-49c0-9876-4cc2fe56244b","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — update the SDK version:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update both base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # verify SDK 11.0.100 is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # confirm it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests if any\n```\n\nAlso update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions in your `.csproj` or via `dotnet outdated`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df129b3d-1287-4355-886f-a7f53f01ed6a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"B016:371ABE:C50F2E:E53F5A:69F2B440"},"id":"b2d37b5e-fb04-404f-82b3-d6c485dca042","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:45:43.280Z","parentId":"dd6bda86-1e09-4f28-a4d5-b539a80bfd68"}
